entries.entry: Today we discussed dot notation v. bracket notation. Both seem very straight forward to me, and i feel more comfortable using dot notation and it seems to be able to do more so I'll probably use that predominantly.

Today we finally discussed scope and variables. I now realize why var isn't used much anymore. I solidified using 'let' 'const' and 'var' later on that night when I was playing around with scopes and inserting different declarations in to see which could move up/down in scope

entries.concepts: Passing a function through a function
entries.entry: Today we learned about passing a function through a function. This was a very clear concept to me as it reminded me of old logic games i used to play while studying for the LSATS.
